up, ill educated’ (Latin  <i>male doctus</i>)."]}]},{"name":"Thomas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir Thomas de Mauduit of Warminster and Shalden was born on 14 October 1287, in Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Warren Mauduit, was 33 and his mother, Elizabeth de Lisle, was 27. He married Eleanor Knoville about 1305, in England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died on 22 March 1321, in his hometown, at the age of 33."},"et":{"14 October 1287–22 March 1321":"14. oktoober 1287–22. märts 1321","1287–1321":"1287–1321","1290–Female":"1290–Surnud","1310–1348":"1310–1348","1254–1300":"1254–1300","1260–1300":"1260–1300","2 February 1310":"2. veebruar 1310","26 Sep 1300":"26. september 1300","1260":"1260","1290":"1290","15 October 1287":"15. oktoober 1287","1348":"1348","14 October 1287":"14. oktoober 1287","about 1305":"umbes 1305","1300":"1300","1310":"1310","1321":"1321","1254":"1254","1287":"1287","about 1300":"umbes 1300","22 March 1321":"22. märts 1321","about 1286":"umbes 1286","Warminster, Wiltshire, England":"Warminster, Wiltshire, England","Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Warminister,,Wiltshire,England":"Wiltshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Gower Hill, Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"14 October 1287–22 March 1321":"14. lokakuuta 1287–22. maaliskuuta 1321","1287–1321":"1287–1321","1290–Female":"1290–Kuollut","1310–1348":"1310